Sentencas: In this work, the new application of cooperation search algorithm (CSA) is addressed to extract the unknown solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)'s parameters supported by investigating and testing the cell steady-state and dynamic performances.
Titulo: Cooperation search algorithm for optimal parameters identification of SOFCs feeding electric vehicle at steady and dynamic modes

Sentencas: Primarily, the indefinite SOFC's parameters are estimated utilizing CSA and the results are assessed and verified with compulsory comparisons.
Titulo: Cooperation search algorithm for optimal parameters identification of SOFCs feeding electric vehicle at steady and dynamic modes

Sentencas: The minimum errors are obtained, CSA convergence behavior and SOFC's performance are all compared with other recognized algorithms in the literature.
Titulo: Cooperation search algorithm for optimal parameters identification of SOFCs feeding electric vehicle at steady and dynamic modes

Sentencas: At last, and for more validations, the dynamic behavior of the SOFCs is studied when supplying electric vehicle (EV) operated with four DC motors at different speeds.
Titulo: Cooperation search algorithm for optimal parameters identification of SOFCs feeding electric vehicle at steady and dynamic modes

Sentencas: The SOFCs and EV are represented via Simulink/MATLAB package.
Titulo: Cooperation search algorithm for optimal parameters identification of SOFCs feeding electric vehicle at steady and dynamic modes

Sentencas: The EV's input current, voltage, power, and torque are traced at various acceleration and speed according to the road nature and/or driver requirements.
Titulo: Cooperation search algorithm for optimal parameters identification of SOFCs feeding electric vehicle at steady and dynamic modes

Sentencas: The extensive investigations and validations prove the high efficacy of CSA capabilities in representing the SOFCs and for analyzing their steady-state and dynamic behaviors.
Titulo: Cooperation search algorithm for optimal parameters identification of SOFCs feeding electric vehicle at steady and dynamic modes
